<article>
  <articleinfo>
    <author>
      <firstname>T. V.</firstname>
      <surname>Raman</surname>
    </author>
    <title>Tips And Tricks For The Emacspeak Audio Desktop
    </title>
    <abstract>
      This document is a collection of tips for using the
      Emacspeak audio desktop.
    </abstract>
  </articleinfo>
  
  <qandaset>
    <title>Productivity Tips</title>
    <qandadiv>
      <title>Online Help</title>
      <qandaentry>
        <question>
          Learning online hypertext help system.
        </question>
        <answer>
          <para>
            Invoke the online hypertext help system by pressing 
            <emphasis><keycombo moreinfo="none"> C-h i
              </keycombo> </emphasis>.
            Press <emphasis><keycap
                                    moreinfo="none">h</keycap></emphasis>
            when using the <application
                                        moreinfo="none">Info System</application> 
            to obtain a primer for first time users.
          </para>
        </answer>
      </qandaentry>
      <qandaentry>
        <question>
Opening info page that documents command invoked by a given key.
        </question>
        <answer>
          <para>
            Press <emphasis><keycombo moreinfo="none"> C-h
            C-k              </keycombo> </emphasis>
followed by the key whose documentation you wish to locate.
</para>
        </answer>
      </qandaentry>
    </qandadiv>

    <qandadiv>
      <title>Files And Folders</title>
      <qandaentry>
        <question>
Working on files and folders.
        </question>
        <answer>
          <para>
            Use command <command
            moreinfo="none">dired</command>
            (directory editor) normally bound to
            <emphasis><keycombo moreinfo="none">
C-x d              </keycombo>
</emphasis> to operate on files and folders.
</para>
        </answer>
      </qandaentry>
      <qandaentry>
        <question>
          Locating files.
        </question>
        <answer>
          <para>
            Use <command moreinfo="none">locate</command>
            and <command
            moreinfo="none">locate-with-filter</command> to
            find files and folders on your hard drive.
            Matching files and folders are displayed using
            the same interface as provided by command
            <command moreinfo="none">dired</command>.  These
            commands use the <database
            moreinfo="none">locate database</database> that
            is typically rebuilt nightly on standard Linux
            systems.
</para>
        </answer>
      </qandaentry>
      <qandaentry>
        <question>
          Using UNIX find from within Emacs.
        </question>
        <answer>
          <para>
            Use commands
             <command
             moreinfo="none">find-name-dired</command>,
            <command
             moreinfo="none">find-grep-dired</command>
            and <command
             moreinfo="none">find-dired</command>
            to use UNIX <application
             moreinfo="none">find</application>
to locate files and folders on your hard drive.
</para>
        </answer>
      </qandaentry>
    </qandadiv>
  </qandaset>
</article>

